HEADWORD: Restrictive
<hw>Re*strict"ive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>restrictif</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Serving or tending to restrict; limiting; <as>as, a
<ex>restrictive</ex> particle; <ex>restrictive</ex> laws of
trade.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Astringent or styptic in effect.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Wiseman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>--<wordforms><wf>Re*strict"ive*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Re*strict"ive*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Restringe</ent>⟦br⟧
